"Mima K.","Inertial fusion power development: The path to global warming suppression",2010,"Nuclear Fusion","50","1", 014006,"","",,,10.1088/0029-5515/50/1/014006,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-76749146130&partnerID=40&md5=729032fec4a1b46a557cbf494b18ed99","Institute of Laser Engineering, Osaka University, 2-6 Yamada-oka Suita, Osaka 565-0871, Japan; Graduate School for the Creation of New Photonics Industries, 1955-1 Kurematsu, Hamamatsu, Nishiku, Sizuoka 431-1202, Japan; Institute of Nuclear Fusion, University Politecnic de Madrid, J.Abascal, 2, Madrid 28006, Spain","Mima, K., Institute of Laser Engineering, Osaka University, 2-6 Yamada-oka Suita, Osaka 565-0871, Japan, Graduate School for the Creation of New Photonics Industries, 1955-1 Kurematsu, Hamamatsu, Nishiku, Sizuoka 431-1202, Japan, Institute of Nuclear Fusion, University Politecnic de Madrid, J.Abascal, 2, Madrid 28006, Spain","Shortly after the demonstration of the first lasers, it was proposed that nuclear fusion induced by laser energized implosion could be utilized for energy generation. Today, there are many facilities worldwide undertaking IFE research, and after decades of experiments, theoretical developments and simulations, it is expected that the laser fusion ignition will be demonstrated in the next few years. If this does indeed happen, we will see a new era toward the realization of a fusion power plant. © 2010 IAEA, Vienna.",,"Energy generations; Fusion power plant; Inertial fusion; Nuclear fusion; Theoretical development; Global warming; Laser fusion",,,,,,"Nuckolls, J., Wood, L., Thiessen, A., Zimmerman, G., Laser compression of matter to super-high densities: Thermonuclear applications (1972) Nature, 239, p. 139; Guderley, G., (1942) Luftfahrtforschung, 19, p. 302; Basov, N.G., Krohin, O.N., (1963) Proc. 3rd IQEC, 2, p. 1373. , (Paris, France); Dawson, J.M., (1964) Phys. Fluids, 7, p. 981; Hora, H., (1969) Proc. Laser Interaction and Related Plasma Phenomena, p. 36